    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>
                <add>רע אהוב עתה כמו מאז צפון מתחת לציון הל"ז</add>
            </p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>
                <add>יצחק בחור וטוב אשר נסעת</add>
            </p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><date>Thursday, Pericope</date>,</p>
            <p rend="align(right)">M'tzorang (<date>March</date>)</p>
            <p>
                <add>מעמק הבכה מושב ההבל</add>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(11)"><placeName>New York</placeName>, <date>1864</date>.</p>
            <p>To the excellent <addressee>Rabbi Eliezar Lippman</addressee><lb/>
                <addressee>Leeser</addressee> of the Sephardic Congregation: I<lb/> received your
                kind letter today, and I<lb/> reply that I can send you a Sefer Torah,<lb/> about 28
                inches in size, not new. It<lb/> will amount to at least $90. This<lb/> I shall do
                for the sake of my dear trusting<lb/> friends so that the Goyim might not<lb/>
                say____. And as to why I have<lb/> not yet sent the T'phillin, please believe<lb/>
                me that I have not received the things<lb/> from the workmen for they are
                overloaded<lb/> with work and this is a secondary matter<lb/> with them. With regard
                to the Sefer Torah,<lb/> reply to me at once and I shall take some<lb/> time to look
                through it and<lb/> correct what mistakes I find; so as to<lb/> send it to you
                “Kosher” Then I shall<lb/> order a new “Etz Chaim” (The wooden rollers),<lb/> so
                that it might reach you in<lb/> proper shape. At the same time I'll send<lb/> some
                T'phillim, mezuzot, and Tsizit.<lb/>
                <del>If you will</del> Reply to me at once, so that</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>you will receive the Sefer Torah before<lb/>
                <date>Passover</date>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I hope to receive your answer.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Your friend <sic>an</sic> Servant,</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">Elijah</persName>, son of
                    <persName>Moses</persName>, Scribe.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">E. M. Holzman</persName>.</p>
            <p>I request an immediate answer, in<lb/> order that I may justify myself; if<lb/> not
                    <del>you will receive the Sefer Torah only</del> then we will be able to see
                each other<lb/> only after <date>Passover</date>, when, God willing,<lb/> I shall be
                in <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>. At that time<lb/> I hope, I shall be able to
                make my<lb/> enemies, “look like the rim of a pot,”<lb/> and God will grant you
                goodness and<lb/> life and that you will celebrate the<lb/>
                <date>passover</date> in joy.</p>
        </body>
